4997OverflowResult llvm::computeOverflowForSignedAdd(const AddOperator *Add,
4998 const DataLayout &DL,
4999 AssumptionCache *AC,
5000 const Instruction *CxtI,
5001 const DominatorTree *DT) {
5002 return ::computeOverflowForSignedAdd(Add->getOperand(0), Add->getOperand(1),
5003 Add, DL, AC, CxtI, DT);
5004}
5005
5006OverflowResult llvm::computeOverflowForSignedAdd(const Value *LHS,
5007 const Value *RHS,
5008 const DataLayout &DL,
5009 AssumptionCache *AC,
5010 const Instruction *CxtI,
5011 const DominatorTree *DT) {
5012 return ::computeOverflowForSignedAdd(LHS, RHS, nullptr, DL, AC, CxtI, DT);
5013}
5014
5015bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(const Instruction *I) {
5016 // Note: An atomic operation isn't guaranteed to return in a reasonable amount
5017 // of time because it's possible for another thread to interfere with it for an
5018 // arbitrary length of time, but programs aren't allowed to rely on that.
5019
5020 // If there is no successor, then execution can't transfer to it.
5021 if (isa<ReturnInst>(I))
5022 return false;
5023 if (isa<UnreachableInst>(I))
5024 return false;
5025
5026 // An instruction that returns without throwing must transfer control flow
5027 // to a successor.
5028 return !I->mayThrow() && I->willReturn();
5029}
5030
5031bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(const BasicBlock *BB) {
5032 // TODO: This is slightly conservative for invoke instruction since exiting
5033 // via an exception *is* normal control for them.
5034 for (auto I = BB->begin(), E = BB->end(); I != E; ++I)
5035 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&*I))
5036 return false;
5037 return true;
5038}
5039
5040bool llvm::isGuaranteedToExecuteForEveryIteration(const Instruction *I,
5041 const Loop *L) {
5042 // The loop header is guaranteed to be executed for every iteration.
5043 //
5044 // FIXME: Relax this constraint to cover all basic blocks that are
5045 // guaranteed to be executed at every iteration.
5046 if (I->getParent() != L->getHeader()) return false;
5047
5048 for (const Instruction &LI : *L->getHeader()) {
5049 if (&LI == I) return true;
5050 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&LI)) return false;
5051 }
5052 llvm_unreachable("Instruction not contained in its own parent basic block.");
5053}
5054
5055bool llvm::propagatesPoison(const Operator *I) {
5056 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
5057 case Instruction::Freeze:
5058 case Instruction::Select:
5059 case Instruction::PHI:
5060 case Instruction::Call:
5061 case Instruction::Invoke:
5062 return false;
5063 case Instruction::ICmp:
5064 case Instruction::FCmp:
5065 case Instruction::GetElementPtr:
5066 return true;
5067 default:
5068 if (isa<BinaryOperator>(I) || isa<UnaryOperator>(I) || isa<CastInst>(I))
5069 return true;
5070
5071 // Be conservative and return false.
5072 return false;
5073 }
5074}
5075
5076void llvm::getGuaranteedNonPoisonOps(const Instruction *I,
5077 SmallPtrSetImpl<const Value *> &Operands) {
5078 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
5079 case Instruction::Store:
5080 Operands.insert(cast<StoreInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
5081 break;
5082
5083 case Instruction::Load:
5084 Operands.insert(cast<LoadInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
5085 break;
5086
5087 case Instruction::AtomicCmpXchg:
5088 Operands.insert(cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
5089 break;
5090
5091 case Instruction::AtomicRMW:
5092 Operands.insert(cast<AtomicRMWInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
5093 break;
5094
5095 case Instruction::UDiv:
5096 case Instruction::SDiv:
5097 case Instruction::URem:
5098 case Instruction::SRem:
5099 Operands.insert(I->getOperand(1));
5100 break;
5101
5102 case Instruction::Call:
5103 case Instruction::Invoke: {
5104 const CallBase *CB = cast<CallBase>(I);
5105 if (CB->isIndirectCall())
5106 Operands.insert(CB->getCalledOperand());
5107 for (unsigned i = 0; i < CB->arg_size(); ++i) {
5108 if (CB->paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::NoUndef))
5109 Operands.insert(CB->getArgOperand(i));
5110 }
5111 break;
5112 }
5113
5114 default:
5115 break;
5116 }
5117}
5118
5119bool llvm::mustTriggerUB(const Instruction *I,
5120 const SmallSet<const Value *, 16>& KnownPoison) {
5121 SmallPtrSet<const Value *, 4> NonPoisonOps;
5122 getGuaranteedNonPoisonOps(I, NonPoisonOps);
5123
5124 for (const auto *V : NonPoisonOps)
5125 if (KnownPoison.count(V))
5126 return true;
5127
5128 return false;
5129}
5130
5131static bool programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(const Value *V,
5132 bool PoisonOnly) {
5133 // We currently only look for uses of values within the same basic
5134 // block, as that makes it easier to guarantee that the uses will be
5135 // executed given that Inst is executed.
5136 //
5137 // FIXME: Expand this to consider uses beyond the same basic block. To do
5138 // this, look out for the distinction between post-dominance and strong
5139 // post-dominance.
5140 const BasicBlock *BB = nullptr;
5141 BasicBlock::const_iterator Begin;
5142 if (const auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
5143 BB = Inst->getParent();
5144 Begin = Inst->getIterator();
5145 Begin++;
5146 } else if (const auto *Arg = dyn_cast<Argument>(V)) {
5147 BB = &Arg->getParent()->getEntryBlock();
5148 Begin = BB->begin();
5149 } else {
5150 return false;
5151 }
5152
5153 BasicBlock::const_iterator End = BB->end();
5154
5155 if (!PoisonOnly) {
5156 // Be conservative & just check whether a value is passed to a noundef
5157 // argument.
5158 // Instructions that raise UB with a poison operand are well-defined
5159 // or have unclear semantics when the input is partially undef.
5160 // For example, 'udiv x, (undef | 1)' isn't UB.
5161
5162 for (auto &I : make_range(Begin, End)) {
5163 if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I)) {
5164 for (unsigned i = 0; i < CB->arg_size(); ++i) {
5165 if (CB->paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::NoUndef) &&
5166 CB->getArgOperand(i) == V)
5167 return true;
5168 }
5169 }
5170 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
5171 break;
5172 }
5173 return false;
5174 }
5175
5176 // Set of instructions that we have proved will yield poison if Inst
5177 // does.
5178 SmallSet<const Value *, 16> YieldsPoison;
5179 SmallSet<const BasicBlock *, 4> Visited;
5180
5181 YieldsPoison.insert(V);
5182 auto Propagate = [&](const User *User) {
5183 if (propagatesPoison(cast<Operator>(User)))
5184 YieldsPoison.insert(User);
5185 };
5186 for_each(V->users(), Propagate);
5187 Visited.insert(BB);
5188
5189 unsigned Iter = 0;
5190 while (Iter++ < MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth) {
5191 for (auto &I : make_range(Begin, End)) {
5192 if (mustTriggerUB(&I, YieldsPoison))
5193 return true;
5194 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
5195 return false;
5196
5197 // Mark poison that propagates from I through uses of I.
5198 if (YieldsPoison.count(&I))
5199 for_each(I.users(), Propagate);
5200 }
5201
5202 if (auto *NextBB = BB->getSingleSuccessor()) {
5203 if (Visited.insert(NextBB).second) {
5204 BB = NextBB;
5205 Begin = BB->getFirstNonPHI()->getIterator();
5206 End = BB->end();
5207 continue;
5208 }
5209 }
5210
5211 break;
5212 }
5213 return false;
5214}
5215
5216bool llvm::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(const Instruction *Inst) {
5217 return ::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(Inst, false);
5218}
5219
5220bool llvm::programUndefinedIfPoison(const Instruction *Inst) {
5221 return ::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(Inst, true);
5222}
5223
5224static bool isKnownNonNaN(const Value *V, FastMathFlags FMF) {
5225 if (FMF.noNaNs())
5226 return true;
5227
5228 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(V))
5229 return !C->isNaN();
5230
5231 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantDataVector>(V)) {
5232 if (!C->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())
5233 return false;
5234 for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
5235 if (C->getElementAsAPFloat(I).isNaN())
5236 return false;
5237 }
5238 return true;
5239 }
5240
5241 if (isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(V))
5242 return true;
5243
5244 return false;
5245}
5246
5247static bool isKnownNonZero(const Value *V) {
5248 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(V))
5249 return !C->isZero();
5250
5251 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantDataVector>(V)) {
5252 if (!C->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())
5253 return false;
5254 for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
5255 if (C->getElementAsAPFloat(I).isZero())
5256 return false;
5257 }
5258 return true;
5259 }
5260
5261 return false;
5262}
5263
5264/// Match clamp pattern for float types without care about NaNs or signed zeros.
5265/// Given non-min/max outer cmp/select from the clamp pattern this
5266/// function recognizes if it can be substitued by a "canonical" min/max
5267/// pattern.
5268static SelectPatternResult matchFastFloatClamp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
5269 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
5270 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
5271 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS) {
5272 // Try to match
5273 // X < C1 ? C1 : Min(X, C2) --> Max(C1, Min(X, C2))
5274 // X > C1 ? C1 : Max(X, C2) --> Min(C1, Max(X, C2))
5275 // and return description of the outer Max/Min.
5276
5277 // First, check if select has inverse order:
5278 if (CmpRHS == FalseVal) {
5279 std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
5280 Pred = CmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred);
5281 }
5282
5283 // Assume success now. If there's no match, callers should not use these anyway.
5284 LHS = TrueVal;
5285 RHS = FalseVal;
5286
5287 const APFloat *FC1;
5288 if (CmpRHS != TrueVal || !match(CmpRHS, m_APFloat(FC1)) || !FC1->isFinite())
5289 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5290
5291 const APFloat *FC2;
5292 switch (Pred) {
5293 case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
5294 case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
5295 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
5296 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
5297 if (match(FalseVal,
5298 m_CombineOr(m_OrdFMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)),
5299 m_UnordFMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)))) &&
5300 *FC1 < *FC2)
5301 return {SPF_FMAXNUM, SPNB_RETURNS_ANY, false};
5302 break;
5303 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
5304 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
5305 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
5306 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
5307 if (match(FalseVal,
5308 m_CombineOr(m_OrdFMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)),
5309 m_UnordFMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)))) &&
5310 *FC1 > *FC2)
5311 return {SPF_FMINNUM, SPNB_RETURNS_ANY, false};
5312 break;
5313 default:
5314 break;
5315 }
5316
5317 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5318}
5319
5320/// Recognize variations of:
5321/// CLAMP(v,l,h) ==> ((v) < (l) ? (l) : ((v) > (h) ? (h) : (v)))
5322static SelectPatternResult matchClamp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
5323 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
5324 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal) {
5325 // Swap the select operands and predicate to match the patterns below.
5326 if (CmpRHS != TrueVal) {
5327 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
5328 std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
5329 }
5330 const APInt *C1;
5331 if (CmpRHS == TrueVal && match(CmpRHS, m_APInt(C1))) {
5332 const APInt *C2;
5333 // (X <s C1) ? C1 : SMIN(X, C2) ==> SMAX(SMIN(X, C2), C1)
5334 if (match(FalseVal, m_SMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
5335 C1->slt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
5336 return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5337
5338 // (X >s C1) ? C1 : SMAX(X, C2) ==> SMIN(SMAX(X, C2), C1)
5339 if (match(FalseVal, m_SMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
5340 C1->sgt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
5341 return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5342
5343 // (X <u C1) ? C1 : UMIN(X, C2) ==> UMAX(UMIN(X, C2), C1)
5344 if (match(FalseVal, m_UMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
5345 C1->ult(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
5346 return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5347
5348 // (X >u C1) ? C1 : UMAX(X, C2) ==> UMIN(UMAX(X, C2), C1)
5349 if (match(FalseVal, m_UMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
5350 C1->ugt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
5351 return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5352 }
5353 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5354}
5355
5356/// Recognize variations of:
5357/// a < c ? min(a,b) : min(b,c) ==> min(min(a,b),min(b,c))
5358static SelectPatternResult matchMinMaxOfMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
5359 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
5360 Value *TVal, Value *FVal,
5361 unsigned Depth) {
5362 // TODO: Allow FP min/max with nnan/nsz.
5363 assert(CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred) && "Expected integer comparison");
5364
5365 Value *A = nullptr, *B = nullptr;
5366 SelectPatternResult L = matchSelectPattern(TVal, A, B, nullptr, Depth + 1);
5367 if (!SelectPatternResult::isMinOrMax(L.Flavor))
5368 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5369
5370 Value *C = nullptr, *D = nullptr;
5371 SelectPatternResult R = matchSelectPattern(FVal, C, D, nullptr, Depth + 1);
5372 if (L.Flavor != R.Flavor)
5373 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5374
5375 // We have something like: x Pred y ? min(a, b) : min(c, d).
5376 // Try to match the compare to the min/max operations of the select operands.
5377 // First, make sure we have the right compare predicate.
5378 switch (L.Flavor) {
5379 case SPF_SMIN:
5380 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE) {
5381 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
5382 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
5383 }
5384 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
5385 break;
5386 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5387 case SPF_SMAX:
5388 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE) {
5389 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
5390 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
5391 }
5392 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
5393 break;
5394 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5395 case SPF_UMIN:
5396 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE) {
5397 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
5398 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
5399 }
5400 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
5401 break;
5402 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5403 case SPF_UMAX:
5404 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE) {
5405 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
5406 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
5407 }
5408 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
5409 break;
5410 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5411 default:
5412 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5413 }
5414
5415 // If there is a common operand in the already matched min/max and the other
5416 // min/max operands match the compare operands (either directly or inverted),
5417 // then this is min/max of the same flavor.
5418
5419 // a pred c ? m(a, b) : m(c, b) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, b))
5420 // ~c pred ~a ? m(a, b) : m(c, b) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, b))
5421 if (D == B) {
5422 if ((CmpLHS == A && CmpRHS == C) || (match(C, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
5423 match(A, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
5424 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
5425 }
5426 // a pred d ? m(a, b) : m(b, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(b, d))
5427 // ~d pred ~a ? m(a, b) : m(b, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(b, d))
5428 if (C == B) {
5429 if ((CmpLHS == A && CmpRHS == D) || (match(D, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
5430 match(A, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
5431 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
5432 }
5433 // b pred c ? m(a, b) : m(c, a) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, a))
5434 // ~c pred ~b ? m(a, b) : m(c, a) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, a))
5435 if (D == A) {
5436 if ((CmpLHS == B && CmpRHS == C) || (match(C, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
5437 match(B, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
5438 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
5439 }
5440 // b pred d ? m(a, b) : m(a, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(a, d))
5441 // ~d pred ~b ? m(a, b) : m(a, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(a, d))
5442 if (C == A) {
5443 if ((CmpLHS == B && CmpRHS == D) || (match(D, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
5444 match(B, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
5445 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
5446 }
5447
5448 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5449}
5450
5451/// If the input value is the result of a 'not' op, constant integer, or vector
5452/// splat of a constant integer, return the bitwise-not source value.
5453/// TODO: This could be extended to handle non-splat vector integer constants.
5454static Value *getNotValue(Value *V) {
5455 Value *NotV;
5456 if (match(V, m_Not(m_Value(NotV))))
5457 return NotV;
5458
5459 const APInt *C;
5460 if (match(V, m_APInt(C)))
5461 return ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), ~(*C));
5462
5463 return nullptr;
5464}
5465
5466/// Match non-obvious integer minimum and maximum sequences.
5467static SelectPatternResult matchMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
5468 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
5469 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
5470 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
5471 unsigned Depth) {
5472 // Assume success. If there's no match, callers should not use these anyway.
5473 LHS = TrueVal;
5474 RHS = FalseVal;
5475
5476 SelectPatternResult SPR = matchClamp(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal);
5477 if (SPR.Flavor != SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_UNKNOWN)
5478 return SPR;
5479
5480 SPR = matchMinMaxOfMinMax(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, Depth);
5481 if (SPR.Flavor != SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_UNKNOWN)
5482 return SPR;
5483
5484 // Look through 'not' ops to find disguised min/max.
5485 // (X > Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> (~X < ~Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> MIN(~X, ~Y)
5486 // (X < Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> (~X > ~Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> MAX(~X, ~Y)
5487 if (CmpLHS == getNotValue(TrueVal) && CmpRHS == getNotValue(FalseVal)) {
5488 switch (Pred) {
5489 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5490 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5491 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5492 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5493 default: break;
5494 }
5495 }
5496
5497 // (X > Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> (~X < ~Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> MAX(~Y, ~X)
5498 // (X < Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> (~X > ~Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> MIN(~Y, ~X)
5499 if (CmpLHS == getNotValue(FalseVal) && CmpRHS == getNotValue(TrueVal)) {
5500 switch (Pred) {
5501 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5502 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5503 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5504 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5505 default: break;
5506 }
5507 }
5508
5509 if (Pred != CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && Pred != CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
5510 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5511
5512 // Z = X -nsw Y
5513 // (X >s Y) ? 0 : Z ==> (Z >s 0) ? 0 : Z ==> SMIN(Z, 0)
5514 // (X <s Y) ? 0 : Z ==> (Z <s 0) ? 0 : Z ==> SMAX(Z, 0)
5515 if (match(TrueVal, m_Zero()) &&
5516 match(FalseVal, m_NSWSub(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_Specific(CmpRHS))))
5517 return {Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT ? SPF_SMIN : SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5518
5519 // Z = X -nsw Y
5520 // (X >s Y) ? Z : 0 ==> (Z >s 0) ? Z : 0 ==> SMAX(Z, 0)
5521 // (X <s Y) ? Z : 0 ==> (Z <s 0) ? Z : 0 ==> SMIN(Z, 0)
5522 if (match(FalseVal, m_Zero()) &&
5523 match(TrueVal, m_NSWSub(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_Specific(CmpRHS))))
5524 return {Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT ? SPF_SMAX : SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5525
5526 const APInt *C1;
5527 if (!match(CmpRHS, m_APInt(C1)))
5528 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5529
5530 // An unsigned min/max can be written with a signed compare.
5531 const APInt *C2;
5532 if ((CmpLHS == TrueVal && match(FalseVal, m_APInt(C2))) ||
5533 (CmpLHS == FalseVal && match(TrueVal, m_APInt(C2)))) {
5534 // Is the sign bit set?
5535 // (X <s 0) ? X : MAXVAL ==> (X >u MAXVAL) ? X : MAXVAL ==> UMAX
5536 // (X <s 0) ? MAXVAL : X ==> (X >u MAXVAL) ? MAXVAL : X ==> UMIN
5537 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT && C1->isNullValue() &&
5538 C2->isMaxSignedValue())
5539 return {CmpLHS == TrueVal ? SPF_UMAX : SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5540
5541 // Is the sign bit clear?
5542 // (X >s -1) ? MINVAL : X ==> (X <u MINVAL) ? MINVAL : X ==> UMAX
5543 // (X >s -1) ? X : MINVAL ==> (X <u MINVAL) ? X : MINVAL ==> UMIN
5544 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && C1->isAllOnesValue() &&
5545 C2->isMinSignedValue())
5546 return {CmpLHS == FalseVal ? SPF_UMAX : SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5547 }
5548
5549 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5550}
5551
5552bool llvm::isKnownNegation(const Value *X, const Value *Y, bool NeedNSW) {
5553 assert(X && Y && "Invalid operand");
5554
5555 // X = sub (0, Y) || X = sub nsw (0, Y)
5556 if ((!NeedNSW && match(X, m_Sub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(Y)))) ||
5557 (NeedNSW && match(X, m_NSWSub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(Y)))))
5558 return true;
5559
5560 // Y = sub (0, X) || Y = sub nsw (0, X)
5561 if ((!NeedNSW && match(Y, m_Sub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(X)))) ||
5562 (NeedNSW && match(Y, m_NSWSub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(X)))))
5563 return true;
5564
5565 // X = sub (A, B), Y = sub (B, A) || X = sub nsw (A, B), Y = sub nsw (B, A)
5566 Value *A, *B;
5567 return (!NeedNSW && (match(X, m_Sub(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
5568 match(Y, m_Sub(m_Specific(B), m_Specific(A))))) ||
5569 (NeedNSW && (match(X, m_NSWSub(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
5570 match(Y, m_NSWSub(m_Specific(B), m_Specific(A)))));
5571}
5572
5573static SelectPatternResult matchSelectPattern(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
5574 FastMathFlags FMF,
5575 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
5576 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
5577 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
5578 unsigned Depth) {
5579 if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred)) {
5580 // IEEE-754 ignores the sign of 0.0 in comparisons. So if the select has one
5581 // 0.0 operand, set the compare's 0.0 operands to that same value for the
5582 // purpose of identifying min/max. Disregard vector constants with undefined
5583 // elements because those can not be back-propagated for analysis.
5584 Value *OutputZeroVal = nullptr;
5585 if (match(TrueVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(FalseVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) &&
5586 !cast<Constant>(TrueVal)->containsUndefOrPoisonElement())
5587 OutputZeroVal = TrueVal;
5588 else if (match(FalseVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(TrueVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) &&
5589 !cast<Constant>(FalseVal)->containsUndefOrPoisonElement())
5590 OutputZeroVal = FalseVal;
5591
5592 if (OutputZeroVal) {
5593 if (match(CmpLHS, m_AnyZeroFP()))
5594 CmpLHS = OutputZeroVal;
5595 if (match(CmpRHS, m_AnyZeroFP()))
5596 CmpRHS = OutputZeroVal;
5597 }
5598 }
5599
5600 LHS = CmpLHS;
5601 RHS = CmpRHS;
5602
5603 // Signed zero may return inconsistent results between implementations.
5604 // (0.0 <= -0.0) ? 0.0 : -0.0 // Returns 0.0
5605 // minNum(0.0, -0.0) // May return -0.0 or 0.0 (IEEE 754-2008 5.3.1)
5606 // Therefore, we behave conservatively and only proceed if at least one of the
5607 // operands is known to not be zero or if we don't care about signed zero.
5608 switch (Pred) {
5609 default: break;
5610 // FIXME: Include OGT/OLT/UGT/ULT.
5611 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
5612 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
5613 if (!FMF.noSignedZeros() && !isKnownNonZero(CmpLHS) &&
5614 !isKnownNonZero(CmpRHS))
5615 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5616 }
5617
5618 SelectPatternNaNBehavior NaNBehavior = SPNB_NA;
5619 bool Ordered = false;
5620
5621 // When given one NaN and one non-NaN input:
5622 // - maxnum/minnum (C99 fmaxf()/fminf()) return the non-NaN input.
5623 // - A simple C99 (a < b ? a : b) construction will return 'b' (as the
5624 // ordered comparison fails), which could be NaN or non-NaN.
5625 // so here we discover exactly what NaN behavior is required/accepted.
5626 if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred)) {
5627 bool LHSSafe = isKnownNonNaN(CmpLHS, FMF);
5628 bool RHSSafe = isKnownNonNaN(CmpRHS, FMF);
5629
5630 if (LHSSafe && RHSSafe) {
5631 // Both operands are known non-NaN.
5632 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_ANY;
5633 } else if (CmpInst::isOrdered(Pred)) {
5634 // An ordered comparison will return false when given a NaN, so it
5635 // returns the RHS.
5636 Ordered = true;
5637 if (LHSSafe)
5638 // LHS is non-NaN, so if RHS is NaN then NaN will be returned.
5639 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
5640 else if (RHSSafe)
5641 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
5642 else
5643 // Completely unsafe.
5644 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5645 } else {
5646 Ordered = false;
5647 // An unordered comparison will return true when given a NaN, so it
5648 // returns the LHS.
5649 if (LHSSafe)
5650 // LHS is non-NaN, so if RHS is NaN then non-NaN will be returned.
5651 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
5652 else if (RHSSafe)
5653 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
5654 else
5655 // Completely unsafe.
5656 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5657 }
5658 }
5659
5660 if (TrueVal == CmpRHS && FalseVal == CmpLHS) {
5661 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
5662 Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
5663 if (NaNBehavior == SPNB_RETURNS_NAN)
5664 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
5665 else if (NaNBehavior == SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER)
5666 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
5667 Ordered = !Ordered;
5668 }
5669
5670 // ([if]cmp X, Y) ? X : Y
5671 if (TrueVal == CmpLHS && FalseVal == CmpRHS) {
5672 switch (Pred) {
5673 default: return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false}; // Equality.
5674 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
5675 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5676 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
5677 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5678 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
5679 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5680 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
5681 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5682 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
5683 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
5684 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
5685 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE: return {SPF_FMAXNUM, NaNBehavior, Ordered};
5686 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
5687 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
5688 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
5689 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE: return {SPF_FMINNUM, NaNBehavior, Ordered};
5690 }
5691 }
5692
5693 if (isKnownNegation(TrueVal, FalseVal)) {
5694 // Sign-extending LHS does not change its sign, so TrueVal/FalseVal can
5695 // match against either LHS or sext(LHS).
5696 auto MaybeSExtCmpLHS =
5697 m_CombineOr(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_SExt(m_Specific(CmpLHS)));
5698 auto ZeroOrAllOnes = m_CombineOr(m_ZeroInt(), m_AllOnes());
5699 auto ZeroOrOne = m_CombineOr(m_ZeroInt(), m_One());
5700 if (match(TrueVal, MaybeSExtCmpLHS)) {
5701 // Set the return values. If the compare uses the negated value (-X >s 0),
5702 // swap the return values because the negated value is always 'RHS'.
5703 LHS = TrueVal;
5704 RHS = FalseVal;
5705 if (match(CmpLHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(FalseVal))))
5706 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
5707
5708 // (X >s 0) ? X : -X or (X >s -1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
5709 // (-X >s 0) ? -X : X or (-X >s -1) ? -X : X --> ABS(X)
5710 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrAllOnes))
5711 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5712
5713 // (X >=s 0) ? X : -X or (X >=s 1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
5714 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
5715 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5716
5717 // (X <s 0) ? X : -X or (X <s 1) ? X : -X --> NABS(X)
5718 // (-X <s 0) ? -X : X or (-X <s 1) ? -X : X --> NABS(X)
5719 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
5720 return {SPF_NABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5721 }
5722 else if (match(FalseVal, MaybeSExtCmpLHS)) {
5723 // Set the return values. If the compare uses the negated value (-X >s 0),
5724 // swap the return values because the negated value is always 'RHS'.
5725 LHS = FalseVal;
5726 RHS = TrueVal;
5727 if (match(CmpLHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(TrueVal))))
5728 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
5729
5730 // (X >s 0) ? -X : X or (X >s -1) ? -X : X --> NABS(X)
5731 // (-X >s 0) ? X : -X or (-X >s -1) ? X : -X --> NABS(X)
5732 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrAllOnes))
5733 return {SPF_NABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5734
5735 // (X <s 0) ? -X : X or (X <s 1) ? -X : X --> ABS(X)
5736 // (-X <s 0) ? X : -X or (-X <s 1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
5737 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
5738 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5739 }
5740 }
5741
5742 if (CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred))
5743 return matchMinMax(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS, Depth);
5744
5745 // According to (IEEE 754-2008 5.3.1), minNum(0.0, -0.0) and similar
5746 // may return either -0.0 or 0.0, so fcmp/select pair has stricter
5747 // semantics than minNum. Be conservative in such case.
5748 if (NaNBehavior != SPNB_RETURNS_ANY ||
5749 (!FMF.noSignedZeros() && !isKnownNonZero(CmpLHS) &&
5750 !isKnownNonZero(CmpRHS)))
5751 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5752
5753 return matchFastFloatClamp(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS);
5754}
5755
5756/// Helps to match a select pattern in case of a type mismatch.
5757///
5758/// The function processes the case when type of true and false values of a
5759/// select instruction differs from type of the cmp instruction operands because
5760/// of a cast instruction. The function checks if it is legal to move the cast
5761/// operation after "select". If yes, it returns the new second value of
5762/// "select" (with the assumption that cast is moved):
5763/// 1. As operand of cast instruction when both values of "select" are same cast
5764/// instructions.
5765/// 2. As restored constant (by applying reverse cast operation) when the first
5766/// value of the "select" is a cast operation and the second value is a
5767/// constant.
5768/// NOTE: We return only the new second value because the first value could be
5769/// accessed as operand of cast instruction.
5770static Value *lookThroughCast(CmpInst *CmpI, Value *V1, Value *V2,
5771 Instruction::CastOps *CastOp) {
5772 auto *Cast1 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V1);
5773 if (!Cast1)
5774 return nullptr;
5775
5776 *CastOp = Cast1->getOpcode();
5777 Type *SrcTy = Cast1->getSrcTy();
5778 if (auto *Cast2 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V2)) {
5779 // If V1 and V2 are both the same cast from the same type, look through V1.
5780 if (*CastOp == Cast2->getOpcode() && SrcTy == Cast2->getSrcTy())
5781 return Cast2->getOperand(0);
5782 return nullptr;
5783 }
5784
5785 auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V2);
5786 if (!C)
5787 return nullptr;
5788
5789 Constant *CastedTo = nullptr;
5790 switch (*CastOp) {
5791 case Instruction::ZExt:
5792 if (CmpI->isUnsigned())
5793 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy);
5794 break;
5795 case Instruction::SExt:
5796 if (CmpI->isSigned())
5797 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy, true);
5798 break;
5799 case Instruction::Trunc:
5800 Constant *CmpConst;
5801 if (match(CmpI->getOperand(1), m_Constant(CmpConst)) &&
5802 CmpConst->getType() == SrcTy) {
5803 // Here we have the following case:
5804 //
5805 // %cond = cmp iN %x, CmpConst
5806 // %tr = trunc iN %x to iK
5807 // %narrowsel = select i1 %cond, iK %t, iK C
5808 //
5809 // We can always move trunc after select operation:
5810 //
5811 // %cond = cmp iN %x, CmpConst
5812 // %widesel = select i1 %cond, iN %x, iN CmpConst
5813 // %tr = trunc iN %widesel to iK
5814 //
5815 // Note that C could be extended in any way because we don't care about
5816 // upper bits after truncation. It can't be abs pattern, because it would
5817 // look like:
5818 //
5819 // select i1 %cond, x, -x.
5820 //
5821 // So only min/max pattern could be matched. Such match requires widened C
5822 // == CmpConst. That is why set widened C = CmpConst, condition trunc
5823 // CmpConst == C is checked below.
5824 CastedTo = CmpConst;
5825 } else {
5826 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(C, SrcTy, CmpI->isSigned());
5827 }
5828 break;
5829 case Instruction::FPTrunc:
5830 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPExtend(C, SrcTy, true);
5831 break;
5832 case Instruction::FPExt:
5833 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPTrunc(C, SrcTy, true);
5834 break;
5835 case Instruction::FPToUI:
5836 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getUIToFP(C, SrcTy, true);
5837 break;
5838 case Instruction::FPToSI:
5839 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getSIToFP(C, SrcTy, true);
5840 break;
5841 case Instruction::UIToFP:
5842 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPToUI(C, SrcTy, true);
5843 break;
5844 case Instruction::SIToFP:
5845 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPToSI(C, SrcTy, true);
5846 break;
5847 default:
5848 break;
5849 }
5850
5851 if (!CastedTo)
5852 return nullptr;
5853
5854 // Make sure the cast doesn't lose any information.
5855 Constant *CastedBack =
5856 ConstantExpr::getCast(*CastOp, CastedTo, C->getType(), true);
5857 if (CastedBack != C)
5858 return nullptr;
5859
5860 return CastedTo;
5861}
5862
5863SelectPatternResult llvm::matchSelectPattern(Value *V, Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
5864 Instruction::CastOps *CastOp,
5865 unsigned Depth) {
5866 if (Depth >= MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
5867 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5868
5869 SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V);
5870 if (!SI) return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5871
5872 CmpInst *CmpI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(SI->getCondition());
5873 if (!CmpI) return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5874
5875 Value *TrueVal = SI->getTrueValue();
5876 Value *FalseVal = SI->getFalseValue();
5877
5878 return llvm::matchDecomposedSelectPattern(CmpI, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS,
5879 CastOp, Depth);
5880}
5881
5882SelectPatternResult llvm::matchDecomposedSelectPattern(
5883 CmpInst *CmpI, Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal, Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
5884 Instruction::CastOps *CastOp, unsigned Depth) {
5885 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = CmpI->getPredicate();
5886 Value *CmpLHS = CmpI->getOperand(0);
5887 Value *CmpRHS = CmpI->getOperand(1);
5888 FastMathFlags FMF;
5889 if (isa<FPMathOperator>(CmpI))
5890 FMF = CmpI->getFastMathFlags();
5891
5892 // Bail out early.
5893 if (CmpI->isEquality())
5894 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5895
5896 // Deal with type mismatches.
5897 if (CastOp && CmpLHS->getType() != TrueVal->getType()) {
5898 if (Value *C = lookThroughCast(CmpI, TrueVal, FalseVal, CastOp)) {
5899 // If this is a potential fmin/fmax with a cast to integer, then ignore
5900 // -0.0 because there is no corresponding integer value.
5901 if (*CastOp == Instruction::FPToSI || *CastOp == Instruction::FPToUI)
5902 FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
5903 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS,
5904 cast<CastInst>(TrueVal)->getOperand(0), C,
5905 LHS, RHS, Depth);
5906 }
5907 if (Value *C = lookThroughCast(CmpI, FalseVal, TrueVal, CastOp)) {
5908 // If this is a potential fmin/fmax with a cast to integer, then ignore
5909 // -0.0 because there is no corresponding integer value.
5910 if (*CastOp == Instruction::FPToSI || *CastOp == Instruction::FPToUI)
5911 FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
5912 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS,
5913 C, cast<CastInst>(FalseVal)->getOperand(0),
5914 LHS, RHS, Depth);
5915 }
5916 }
5917 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal,
5918 LHS, RHS, Depth);
5919}
5920
5921CmpInst::Predicate llvm::getMinMaxPred(SelectPatternFlavor SPF, bool Ordered) {
5922 if (SPF == SPF_SMIN) return ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
5923 if (SPF == SPF_UMIN) return ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
5924 if (SPF == SPF_SMAX) return ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT;
5925 if (SPF == SPF_UMAX) return ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
5926 if (SPF == SPF_FMINNUM)
5927 return Ordered ? FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT : FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT;
5928 if (SPF == SPF_FMAXNUM)
5929 return Ordered ? FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT : FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT;
5930 llvm_unreachable("unhandled!");
5931}
5932
5933SelectPatternFlavor llvm::getInverseMinMaxFlavor(SelectPatternFlavor SPF) {
5934 if (SPF == SPF_SMIN) return SPF_SMAX;
5935 if (SPF == SPF_UMIN) return SPF_UMAX;
5936 if (SPF == SPF_SMAX) return SPF_SMIN;
5937 if (SPF == SPF_UMAX) return SPF_UMIN;
5938 llvm_unreachable("unhandled!");
5939}
5940
5941CmpInst::Predicate llvm::getInverseMinMaxPred(SelectPatternFlavor SPF) {
5942 return getMinMaxPred(getInverseMinMaxFlavor(SPF));
5943}
5944
5945std::pair<Intrinsic::ID, bool>
5946llvm::canConvertToMinOrMaxIntrinsic(ArrayRef<Value *> VL) {
5947 // Check if VL contains select instructions that can be folded into a min/max
5948 // vector intrinsic and return the intrinsic if it is possible.
5949 // TODO: Support floating point min/max.
5950 bool AllCmpSingleUse = true;
5951 SelectPatternResult SelectPattern;
5952 SelectPattern.Flavor = SPF_UNKNOWN;
5953 if (all_of(VL, [&SelectPattern, &AllCmpSingleUse](Value *I) {
5954 Value *LHS, *RHS;
5955 auto CurrentPattern = matchSelectPattern(I, LHS, RHS);
5956 if (!SelectPatternResult::isMinOrMax(CurrentPattern.Flavor) ||
5957 CurrentPattern.Flavor == SPF_FMINNUM ||
5958 CurrentPattern.Flavor == SPF_FMAXNUM ||
5959 !I->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
5960 return false;
5961 if (SelectPattern.Flavor != SPF_UNKNOWN &&
5962 SelectPattern.Flavor != CurrentPattern.Flavor)
5963 return false;
5964 SelectPattern = CurrentPattern;
5965 AllCmpSingleUse &=
5966 match(I, m_Select(m_OneUse(m_Value()), m_Value(), m_Value()));
5967 return true;
5968 })) {
5969 switch (SelectPattern.Flavor) {
5970 case SPF_SMIN:
5971 return {Intrinsic::smin, AllCmpSingleUse};
5972 case SPF_UMIN:
5973 return {Intrinsic::umin, AllCmpSingleUse};
5974 case SPF_SMAX:
5975 return {Intrinsic::smax, AllCmpSingleUse};
5976 case SPF_UMAX:
5977 return {Intrinsic::umax, AllCmpSingleUse};
5978 default:
5979 llvm_unreachable("unexpected select pattern flavor");
5980 }
5981 }
5982 return {Intrinsic::not_intrinsic, false};
5983}
5984
5985/// Return true if "icmp Pred LHS RHS" is always true.
5986static bool isTruePredicate(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, const Value *LHS,
5987 const Value *RHS, const DataLayout &DL,
5988 unsigned Depth) {
5989 assert(!LHS->getType()->isVectorTy() && "TODO: extend to handle vectors!");
5990 if (ICmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred) && LHS == RHS)
5991 return true;
5992
5993 switch (Pred) {
5994 default:
5995 return false;
5996
5997 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE: {
5998 const APInt *C;
5999
6000 // LHS s<= LHS +_{nsw} C if C >= 0
6001 if (match(RHS, m_NSWAdd(m_Specific(LHS), m_APInt(C))))
6002 return !C->isNegative();
6003 return false;
6004 }
6005
6006 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE: {
6007 const APInt *C;
6008
6009 // LHS u<= LHS +_{nuw} C for any C
6010 if (match(RHS, m_NUWAdd(m_Specific(LHS), m_APInt(C))))
6011 return true;
6012
6013 // Match A to (X +_{nuw} CA) and B to (X +_{nuw} CB)
6014 auto MatchNUWAddsToSameValue = [&](const Value *A, const Value *B,
6015 const Value *&X,
6016 const APInt *&CA, const APInt *&CB) {
6017 if (match(A, m_NUWAdd(m_Value(X), m_APInt(CA))) &&
6018 match(B, m_NUWAdd(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(CB))))
6019 return true;
6020
6021 // If X & C == 0 then (X | C) == X +_{nuw} C
6022 if (match(A, m_Or(m_Value(X), m_APInt(CA))) &&
6023 match(B, m_Or(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(CB)))) {
6024 KnownBits Known(CA->getBitWidth());
6025 computeKnownBits(X, Known, DL, Depth + 1, /*AC*/ nullptr,
6026 /*CxtI*/ nullptr, /*DT*/ nullptr);
6027 if (CA->isSubsetOf(Known.Zero) && CB->isSubsetOf(Known.Zero))
6028 return true;
6029 }
6030
6031 return false;
6032 };
6033
6034 const Value *X;
6035 const APInt *CLHS, *CRHS;
6036 if (MatchNUWAddsToSameValue(LHS, RHS, X, CLHS, CRHS))
6037 return CLHS->ule(*CRHS);
6038
6039 return false;
6040 }
6041 }
6042}
6043
6044/// Return true if "icmp Pred BLHS BRHS" is true whenever "icmp Pred
6045/// ALHS ARHS" is true. Otherwise, return None.
6046static Optional<bool>
6047isImpliedCondOperands(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, const Value *ALHS,
6048 const Value *ARHS, const Value *BLHS, const Value *BRHS,
6049 const DataLayout &DL, unsigned Depth) {
6050 switch (Pred) {
6051 default:
6052 return None;
6053
6054 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
6055 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
6056 if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, BLHS, ALHS, DL, Depth) &&
6057 isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, ARHS, BRHS, DL, Depth))
6058 return true;
6059 return None;
6060
6061 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
6062 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
6063 if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, BLHS, ALHS, DL, Depth) &&
6064 isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, ARHS, BRHS, DL, Depth))
6065 return true;
6066 return None;
6067 }
6068}
6069
6070/// Return true if the operands of the two compares match. IsSwappedOps is true
6071/// when the operands match, but are swapped.
6072static bool isMatchingOps(const Value *ALHS, const Value *ARHS,
6073 const Value *BLHS, const Value *BRHS,
6074 bool &IsSwappedOps) {
6075
6076 bool IsMatchingOps = (ALHS == BLHS && ARHS == BRHS);
6077 IsSwappedOps = (ALHS == BRHS && ARHS == BLHS);
6078 return IsMatchingOps || IsSwappedOps;
6079}
6080
6081/// Return true if "icmp1 APred X, Y" implies "icmp2 BPred X, Y" is true.
6082/// Return false if "icmp1 APred X, Y" implies "icmp2 BPred X, Y" is false.
6083/// Otherwise, return None if we can't infer anything.
6084static Optional<bool> isImpliedCondMatchingOperands(CmpInst::Predicate APred,
6085 CmpInst::Predicate BPred,
6086 bool AreSwappedOps) {
6087 // Canonicalize the predicate as if the operands were not commuted.
6088 if (AreSwappedOps)
6089 BPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(BPred);
6090
6091 if (CmpInst::isImpliedTrueByMatchingCmp(APred, BPred))
6092 return true;
6093 if (CmpInst::isImpliedFalseByMatchingCmp(APred, BPred))
6094 return false;
6095
6096 return None;
6097}
6098
6099/// Return true if "icmp APred X, C1" implies "icmp BPred X, C2" is true.
6100/// Return false if "icmp APred X, C1" implies "icmp BPred X, C2" is false.
6101/// Otherwise, return None if we can't infer anything.
6102static Optional<bool>
6103isImpliedCondMatchingImmOperands(CmpInst::Predicate APred,
6104 const ConstantInt *C1,
6105 CmpInst::Predicate BPred,
6106 const ConstantInt *C2) {
6107 ConstantRange DomCR =
6108 ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(APred, C1->getValue());
6109 ConstantRange CR =
6110 ConstantRange::makeAllowedICmpRegion(BPred, C2->getValue());
6111 ConstantRange Intersection = DomCR.intersectWith(CR);
6112 ConstantRange Difference = DomCR.difference(CR);
6113 if (Intersection.isEmptySet())
6114 return false;
6115 if (Difference.isEmptySet())
6116 return true;
6117 return None;
6118}
6119
6120/// Return true if LHS implies RHS is true. Return false if LHS implies RHS is
6121/// false. Otherwise, return None if we can't infer anything.
6122static Optional<bool> isImpliedCondICmps(const ICmpInst *LHS,
6123 CmpInst::Predicate BPred,
6124 const Value *BLHS, const Value *BRHS,
6125 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue,
6126 unsigned Depth) {
6127 Value *ALHS = LHS->getOperand(0);
6128 Value *ARHS = LHS->getOperand(1);
6129
6130 // The rest of the logic assumes the LHS condition is true. If that's not the
6131 // case, invert the predicate to make it so.
6132 CmpInst::Predicate APred =
6133 LHSIsTrue ? LHS->getPredicate() : LHS->getInversePredicate();
6134
6135 // Can we infer anything when the two compares have matching operands?
6136 bool AreSwappedOps;
6137 if (isMatchingOps(ALHS, ARHS, BLHS, BRHS, AreSwappedOps)) {
6138 if (Optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondMatchingOperands(
6139 APred, BPred, AreSwappedOps))
6140 return Implication;
6141 // No amount of additional analysis will infer the second condition, so
6142 // early exit.
6143 return None;
6144 }
6145
6146 // Can we infer anything when the LHS operands match and the RHS operands are
6147 // constants (not necessarily matching)?
6148 if (ALHS == BLHS && isa<ConstantInt>(ARHS) && isa<ConstantInt>(BRHS)) {
6149 if (Optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondMatchingImmOperands(
6150 APred, cast<ConstantInt>(ARHS), BPred, cast<ConstantInt>(BRHS)))
6151 return Implication;
6152 // No amount of additional analysis will infer the second condition, so
6153 // early exit.
6154 return None;
6155 }
6156
6157 if (APred == BPred)
6158 return isImpliedCondOperands(APred, ALHS, ARHS, BLHS, BRHS, DL, Depth);
6159 return None;
6160}
6161
6162/// Return true if LHS implies RHS is true. Return false if LHS implies RHS is
6163/// false. Otherwise, return None if we can't infer anything. We expect the
6164/// RHS to be an icmp and the LHS to be an 'and', 'or', or a 'select' instruction.
6165static Optional<bool>
6166isImpliedCondAndOr(const Instruction *LHS, CmpInst::Predicate RHSPred,
6167 const Value *RHSOp0, const Value *RHSOp1,
6168 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
6169 // The LHS must be an 'or', 'and', or a 'select' instruction.
6170 assert((LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::And ||
6171 LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or ||
6172 LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Select) &&
6173 "Expected LHS to be 'and', 'or', or 'select'.");
6174
6175 assert(Depth <= MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth && "Hit recursion limit");
6176
6177 // If the result of an 'or' is false, then we know both legs of the 'or' are
6178 // false. Similarly, if the result of an 'and' is true, then we know both
6179 // legs of the 'and' are true.
6180 const Value *ALHS, *ARHS;
6181 if ((!LHSIsTrue && match(LHS, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(ALHS), m_Value(ARHS)))) ||
6182 (LHSIsTrue && match(LHS, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(ALHS), m_Value(ARHS))))) {
6183 // FIXME: Make this non-recursion.
6184 if (Optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondition(
6185 ALHS, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
6186 return Implication;
6187 if (Optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondition(
6188 ARHS, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
6189 return Implication;
6190 return None;
6191 }
6192 return None;
6193}
6194
6195Optional<bool>
6196llvm::isImpliedCondition(const Value *LHS, CmpInst::Predicate RHSPred,
6197 const Value *RHSOp0, const Value *RHSOp1,
6198 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
6199 // Bail out when we hit the limit.
6200 if (Depth == MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
6201 return None;
6202
6203 // A mismatch occurs when we compare a scalar cmp to a vector cmp, for
6204 // example.
6205 if (RHSOp0->getType()->isVectorTy() != LHS->getType()->isVectorTy())
6206 return None;
6207
6208 Type *OpTy = LHS->getType();
6209 assert(OpTy->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) && "Expected integer type only!");
6210
6211 // FIXME: Extending the code below to handle vectors.
6212 if (OpTy->isVectorTy())
6213 return None;
6214
6215 assert(OpTy->isIntegerTy(1) && "implied by above");
6216
6217 // Both LHS and RHS are icmps.
6218 const ICmpInst *LHSCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(LHS);
6219 if (LHSCmp)
6220 return isImpliedCondICmps(LHSCmp, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue,
6221 Depth);
6222
6223 /// The LHS should be an 'or', 'and', or a 'select' instruction. We expect
6224 /// the RHS to be an icmp.
6225 /// FIXME: Add support for and/or/select on the RHS.
6226 if (const Instruction *LHSI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(LHS)) {
6227 if ((LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::And ||
6228 LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or ||
6229 LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::Select))
6230 return isImpliedCondAndOr(LHSI, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue,
6231 Depth);
6232 }
6233 return None;
6234}
6235
6236Optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedCondition(const Value *LHS, const Value *RHS,
6237 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue,
6238 unsigned Depth) {
6239 // LHS ==> RHS by definition
6240 if (LHS == RHS)
6241 return LHSIsTrue;
6242
6243 const ICmpInst *RHSCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(RHS);
6244 if (RHSCmp)
6245 return isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHSCmp->getPredicate(),
6246 RHSCmp->getOperand(0), RHSCmp->getOperand(1), DL,
6247 LHSIsTrue, Depth);
6248 return None;
6249}
6250
6251// Returns a pair (Condition, ConditionIsTrue), where Condition is a branch
6252// condition dominating ContextI or nullptr, if no condition is found.
6253static std::pair<Value *, bool>
6254getDomPredecessorCondition(const Instruction *ContextI) {
6255 if (!ContextI || !ContextI->getParent())
6256 return {nullptr, false};
6257
6258 // TODO: This is a poor/cheap way to determine dominance. Should we use a
6259 // dominator tree (eg, from a SimplifyQuery) instead?
6260 const BasicBlock *ContextBB = ContextI->getParent();
6261 const BasicBlock *PredBB = ContextBB->getSinglePredecessor();
6262 if (!PredBB)
6263 return {nullptr, false};
6264
6265 // We need a conditional branch in the predecessor.
6266 Value *PredCond;
6267 BasicBlock *TrueBB, *FalseBB;
6268 if (!match(PredBB->getTerminator(), m_Br(m_Value(PredCond), TrueBB, FalseBB)))
6269 return {nullptr, false};
6270
6271 // The branch should get simplified. Don't bother simplifying this condition.
6272 if (TrueBB == FalseBB)
6273 return {nullptr, false};
6274
6275 assert((TrueBB == ContextBB || FalseBB == ContextBB) &&
6276 "Predecessor block does not point to successor?");
6277
6278 // Is this condition implied by the predecessor condition?
6279 return {PredCond, TrueBB == ContextBB};
6280}
6281
6282Optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedByDomCondition(const Value *Cond,
6283 const Instruction *ContextI,
6284 const DataLayout &DL) {
6285 assert(Cond->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) && "Condition must be bool");
6286 auto PredCond = getDomPredecessorCondition(ContextI);
6287 if (PredCond.first)
6288 return isImpliedCondition(PredCond.first, Cond, DL, PredCond.second);
6289 return None;
6290}
6291
6292Optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedByDomCondition(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
6293 const Value *LHS, const Value *RHS,
6294 const Instruction *ContextI,
6295 const DataLayout &DL) {
6296 auto PredCond = getDomPredecessorCondition(ContextI);
6297 if (PredCond.first)
6298 return isImpliedCondition(PredCond.first, Pred, LHS, RHS, DL,
6299 PredCond.second);
6300 return None;
6301}
6302
6303static void setLimitsForBinOp(const BinaryOperator &BO, APInt &Lower,
6304 APInt &Upper, const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
6305 unsigned Width = Lower.getBitWidth();
6306 const APInt *C;
6307 switch (BO.getOpcode()) {
6308 case Instruction::Add:
6309 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isNullValue()) {
6310 // FIXME: If we have both nuw and nsw, we should reduce the range further.
6311 if (IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(&BO))) {
6312 // 'add nuw x, C' produces [C, UINT_MAX].
6313 Lower = *C;
6314 } else if (IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(&BO))) {
6315 if (C->isNegative()) {
6316 // 'add nsw x, -C' produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX - C].
6317 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
6318 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + *C + 1;
6319 } else {
6320 // 'add nsw x, +C' produces [SINT_MIN + C, SINT_MAX].
6321 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + *C;
6322 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
6323 }
6324 }
6325 }
6326 break;
6327
6328 case Instruction::And:
6329 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
6330 // 'and x, C' produces [0, C].
6331 Upper = *C + 1;
6332 break;
6333
6334 case Instruction::Or:
6335 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
6336 // 'or x, C' produces [C, UINT_MAX].
6337 Lower = *C;
6338 break;
6339
6340 case Instruction::AShr:
6341 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
6342 // 'ashr x, C' produces [INT_MIN >> C, INT_MAX >> C].
6343 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width).ashr(*C);
6344 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width).ashr(*C) + 1;
6345 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
6346 unsigned ShiftAmount = Width - 1;
6347 if (!C->isNullValue() && IIQ.isExact(&BO))
6348 ShiftAmount = C->countTrailingZeros();
6349 if (C->isNegative()) {
6350 // 'ashr C, x' produces [C, C >> (Width-1)]
6351 Lower = *C;
6352 Upper = C->ashr(ShiftAmount) + 1;
6353 } else {
6354 // 'ashr C, x' produces [C >> (Width-1), C]
6355 Lower = C->ashr(ShiftAmount);
6356 Upper = *C + 1;
6357 }
6358 }
6359 break;
6360
6361 case Instruction::LShr:
6362 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
6363 // 'lshr x, C' produces [0, UINT_MAX >> C].
6364 Upper = APInt::getAllOnesValue(Width).lshr(*C) + 1;
6365 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
6366 // 'lshr C, x' produces [C >> (Width-1), C].
6367 unsigned ShiftAmount = Width - 1;
6368 if (!C->isNullValue() && IIQ.isExact(&BO))
6369 ShiftAmount = C->countTrailingZeros();
6370 Lower = C->lshr(ShiftAmount);
6371 Upper = *C + 1;
6372 }
6373 break;
6374
6375 case Instruction::Shl:
6376 if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
6377 if (IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(&BO)) {
6378 // 'shl nuw C, x' produces [C, C << CLZ(C)]
6379 Lower = *C;
6380 Upper = Lower.shl(Lower.countLeadingZeros()) + 1;
6381 } else if (BO.hasNoSignedWrap()) { // TODO: What if both nuw+nsw?
6382 if (C->isNegative()) {
6383 // 'shl nsw C, x' produces [C << CLO(C)-1, C]
6384 unsigned ShiftAmount = C->countLeadingOnes() - 1;
6385 Lower = C->shl(ShiftAmount);
6386 Upper = *C + 1;
6387 } else {
6388 // 'shl nsw C, x' produces [C, C << CLZ(C)-1]
6389 unsigned ShiftAmount = C->countLeadingZeros() - 1;
6390 Lower = *C;
6391 Upper = C->shl(ShiftAmount) + 1;
6392 }
6393 }
6394 }
6395 break;
6396
6397 case Instruction::SDiv:
6398 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
6399 APInt IntMin = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
6400 APInt IntMax = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width);
6401 if (C->isAllOnesValue()) {
6402 // 'sdiv x, -1' produces [INT_MIN + 1, INT_MAX]
6403 // where C != -1 and C != 0 and C != 1
6404 Lower = IntMin + 1;
6405 Upper = IntMax + 1;
6406 } else if (C->countLeadingZeros() < Width - 1) {
6407 // 'sdiv x, C' produces [INT_MIN / C, INT_MAX / C]
6408 // where C != -1 and C != 0 and C != 1
6409 Lower = IntMin.sdiv(*C);
6410 Upper = IntMax.sdiv(*C);
6411 if (Lower.sgt(Upper))
6412 std::swap(Lower, Upper);
6413 Upper = Upper + 1;
6414 assert(Upper != Lower && "Upper part of range has wrapped!");
6415 }
6416 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
6417 if (C->isMinSignedValue()) {
6418 // 'sdiv INT_MIN, x' produces [INT_MIN, INT_MIN / -2].
6419 Lower = *C;
6420 Upper = Lower.lshr(1) + 1;
6421 } else {
6422 // 'sdiv C, x' produces [-|C|, |C|].
6423 Upper = C->abs() + 1;
6424 Lower = (-Upper) + 1;
6425 }
6426 }
6427 break;
6428
6429 case Instruction::UDiv:
6430 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isNullValue()) {
6431 // 'udiv x, C' produces [0, UINT_MAX / C].
6432 Upper = APInt::getMaxValue(Width).udiv(*C) + 1;
6433 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
6434 // 'udiv C, x' produces [0, C].
6435 Upper = *C + 1;
6436 }
6437 break;
6438
6439 case Instruction::SRem:
6440 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
6441 // 'srem x, C' produces (-|C|, |C|).
6442 Upper = C->abs();
6443 Lower = (-Upper) + 1;
6444 }
6445 break;
6446
6447 case Instruction::URem:
6448 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
6449 // 'urem x, C' produces [0, C).
6450 Upper = *C;
6451 break;
6452
6453 default:
6454 break;
6455 }
6456}
6457
6458static void setLimitsForIntrinsic(const IntrinsicInst &II, APInt &Lower,
6459 APInt &Upper) {
6460 unsigned Width = Lower.getBitWidth();
6461 const APInt *C;
6462 switch (II.getIntrinsicID()) {
6463 case Intrinsic::ctpop:
6464 case Intrinsic::ctlz:
6465 case Intrinsic::cttz:
6466 // Maximum of set/clear bits is the bit width.
6467 assert(Lower == 0 && "Expected lower bound to be zero");
6468 Upper = Width + 1;
6469 break;
6470 case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
6471 // uadd.sat(x, C) produces [C, UINT_MAX].
6472 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) ||
6473 match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
6474 Lower = *C;
6475 break;
6476 case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
6477 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) ||
6478 match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
6479 if (C->isNegative()) {
6480 // sadd.sat(x, -C) produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX + (-C)].
6481 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
6482 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + *C + 1;
6483 } else {
6484 // sadd.sat(x, +C) produces [SINT_MIN + C, SINT_MAX].
6485 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + *C;
6486 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
6487 }
6488 }
6489 break;
6490 case Intrinsic::usub_sat:
6491 // usub.sat(C, x) produces [0, C].
6492 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)))
6493 Upper = *C + 1;
6494 // usub.sat(x, C) produces [0, UINT_MAX - C].
6495 else if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
6496 Upper = APInt::getMaxValue(Width) - *C + 1;
6497 break;
6498 case Intrinsic::ssub_sat:
6499 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
6500 if (C->isNegative()) {
6501 // ssub.sat(-C, x) produces [SINT_MIN, -SINT_MIN + (-C)].
6502 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
6503 Upper = *C - APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + 1;
6504 } else {
6505 // ssub.sat(+C, x) produces [-SINT_MAX + C, SINT_MAX].
6506 Lower = *C - APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width);
6507 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
6508 }
6509 } else if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
6510 if (C->isNegative()) {
6511 // ssub.sat(x, -C) produces [SINT_MIN - (-C), SINT_MAX]:
6512 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) - *C;
6513 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
6514 } else {
6515 // ssub.sat(x, +C) produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX - C].
6516 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
6517 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) - *C + 1;
6518 }
6519 }
6520 break;
6521 case Intrinsic::umin:
6522 case Intrinsic::umax:
6523 case Intrinsic::smin:
6524 case Intrinsic::smax:
6525 if (!match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) &&
6526 !match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
6527 break;
6528
6529 switch (II.getIntrinsicID()) {
6530 case Intrinsic::umin:
6531 Upper = *C + 1;
6532 break;
6533 case Intrinsic::umax:
6534 Lower = *C;
6535 break;
6536 case Intrinsic::smin:
6537 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
6538 Upper = *C + 1;
6539 break;
6540 case Intrinsic::smax:
6541 Lower = *C;
6542 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
6543 break;
6544 default:
6545 llvm_unreachable("Must be min/max intrinsic");
6546 }
6547 break;
6548 case Intrinsic::abs:
6549 // If abs of SIGNED_MIN is poison, then the result is [0..SIGNED_MAX],
6550 // otherwise it is [0..SIGNED_MIN], as -SIGNED_MIN == SIGNED_MIN.
6551 if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_One()))
6552 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
6553 else
6554 Upper = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + 1;
6555 break;
6556 default:
6557 break;
6558 }
6559}
6560
6561static void setLimitsForSelectPattern(const SelectInst &SI, APInt &Lower,
6562 APInt &Upper, const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
6563 const Value *LHS = nullptr, *RHS = nullptr;
6564 SelectPatternResult R = matchSelectPattern(&SI, LHS, RHS);
6565 if (R.Flavor == SPF_UNKNOWN)
6566 return;
6567
6568 unsigned BitWidth = SI.getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
6569
6570 if (R.Flavor == SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_ABS) {
6571 // If the negation part of the abs (in RHS) has the NSW flag,
6572 // then the result of abs(X) is [0..SIGNED_MAX],
6573 // otherwise it is [0..SIGNED_MIN], as -SIGNED_MIN == SIGNED_MIN.
6574 Lower = APInt::getNullValue(BitWidth);
6575 if (match(RHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(LHS))) &&
6576 IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(cast<Instruction>(RHS)))
6577 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) + 1;
6578 else
6579 Upper = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth) + 1;
6580 return;
6581 }
6582
6583 if (R.Flavor == SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_NABS) {
6584 // The result of -abs(X) is <= 0.
6585 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
6586 Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 1);
6587 return;
6588 }
6589
6590 const APInt *C;
6591 if (!match(LHS, m_APInt(C)) && !match(RHS, m_APInt(C)))
6592 return;
6593
6594 switch (R.Flavor) {
6595 case SPF_UMIN:
6596 Upper = *C + 1;
6597 break;
6598 case SPF_UMAX:
6599 Lower = *C;
6600 break;
6601 case SPF_SMIN:
6602 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
6603 Upper = *C + 1;
6604 break;
6605 case SPF_SMAX:
6606 Lower = *C;
6607 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) + 1;
6608 break;
6609 default:
6610 break;
6611 }
6612}
6613
6614ConstantRange llvm::computeConstantRange(const Value *V, bool UseInstrInfo,
6615 AssumptionCache *AC,
6616 const Instruction *CtxI,
6617 unsigned Depth) {
6618 assert(V->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && "Expected integer instruction");
6619
6620 if (Depth == MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
6621 return ConstantRange::getFull(V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits());
6622
6623 const APInt *C;
6624 if (match(V, m_APInt(C)))
6625 return ConstantRange(*C);
6626
6627 InstrInfoQuery IIQ(UseInstrInfo);
6628 unsigned BitWidth = V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
6629 APInt Lower = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
6630 APInt Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
6631 if (auto *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(V))
6632 setLimitsForBinOp(*BO, Lower, Upper, IIQ);
6633 else if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(V))
6634 setLimitsForIntrinsic(*II, Lower, Upper);
6635 else if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V))
6636 setLimitsForSelectPattern(*SI, Lower, Upper, IIQ);
6637
6638 ConstantRange CR = ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(Lower, Upper);
6639
6640 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
6641 if (auto *Range = IIQ.getMetadata(I, LLVMContext::MD_range))
6642 CR = CR.intersectWith(getConstantRangeFromMetadata(*Range));
6643
6644 if (CtxI && AC) {
6645 // Try to restrict the range based on information from assumptions.
6646 for (auto &AssumeVH : AC->assumptionsFor(V)) {
6647 if (!AssumeVH)
6648 continue;
6649 CallInst *I = cast<CallInst>(AssumeVH);
6650 assert(I->getParent()->getParent() == CtxI->getParent()->getParent() &&
6651 "Got assumption for the wrong function!");
6652 assert(I->getCalledFunction()->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::assume &&
6653 "must be an assume intrinsic");
6654
6655 if (!isValidAssumeForContext(I, CtxI, nullptr))
6656 continue;
6657 Value *Arg = I->getArgOperand(0);
6658 ICmpInst *Cmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(Arg);
6659 // Currently we just use information from comparisons.
6660 if (!Cmp || Cmp->getOperand(0) != V)
6661 continue;
6662 ConstantRange RHS = computeConstantRange(Cmp->getOperand(1), UseInstrInfo,
6663 AC, I, Depth + 1);
6664 CR = CR.intersectWith(
6665 ConstantRange::makeSatisfyingICmpRegion(Cmp->getPredicate(), RHS));
6666 }
6667 }
6668
6669 return CR;
6670}
6671
6672static Optional<int64_t>
6673getOffsetFromIndex(const GEPOperator *GEP, unsigned Idx, const DataLayout &DL) {
6674 // Skip over the first indices.
6675 gep_type_iterator GTI = gep_type_begin(GEP);
6676 for (unsigned i = 1; i != Idx; ++i, ++GTI)
6677 /*skip along*/;
6678
6679 // Compute the offset implied by the rest of the indices.
6680 int64_t Offset = 0;
6681 for (unsigned i = Idx, e = GEP->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i, ++GTI) {
6682 ConstantInt *OpC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(GEP->getOperand(i));
6683 if (!OpC)
6684 return None;
6685 if (OpC->isZero())
6686 continue; // No offset.
6687
6688 // Handle struct indices, which add their field offset to the pointer.
6689 if (StructType *STy = GTI.getStructTypeOrNull()) {
6690 Offset += DL.getStructLayout(STy)->getElementOffset(OpC->getZExtValue());
6691 continue;
6692 }
6693
6694 // Otherwise, we have a sequential type like an array or fixed-length
6695 // vector. Multiply the index by the ElementSize.
6696 TypeSize Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GTI.getIndexedType());
6697 if (Size.isScalable())
6698 return None;
6699 Offset += Size.getFixedSize() * OpC->getSExtValue();
6700 }
6701
6702 return Offset;
6703}
6704
6705Optional<int64_t> llvm::isPointerOffset(const Value *Ptr1, const Value *Ptr2,
6706 const DataLayout &DL) {
6707 Ptr1 = Ptr1->stripPointerCasts();
6708 Ptr2 = Ptr2->stripPointerCasts();
6709
6710 // Handle the trivial case first.
6711 if (Ptr1 == Ptr2) {
6712 return 0;
6713 }
6714
6715 const GEPOperator *GEP1 = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(Ptr1);
6716 const GEPOperator *GEP2 = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(Ptr2);
6717
6718 // If one pointer is a GEP see if the GEP is a constant offset from the base,
6719 // as in "P" and "gep P, 1".
6720 // Also do this iteratively to handle the the following case:
6721 // Ptr_t1 = GEP Ptr1, c1
6722 // Ptr_t2 = GEP Ptr_t1, c2
6723 // Ptr2 = GEP Ptr_t2, c3
6724 // where we will return c1+c2+c3.
6725 // TODO: Handle the case when both Ptr1 and Ptr2 are GEPs of some common base
6726 // -- replace getOffsetFromBase with getOffsetAndBase, check that the bases
6727 // are the same, and return the difference between offsets.
6728 auto getOffsetFromBase = [&DL](const GEPOperator *GEP,
6729 const Value *Ptr) -> Optional<int64_t> {
6730 const GEPOperator *GEP_T = GEP;
6731 int64_t OffsetVal = 0;
6732 bool HasSameBase = false;
6733 while (GEP_T) {
6734 auto Offset = getOffsetFromIndex(GEP_T, 1, DL);
6735 if (!Offset)
6736 return None;
6737 OffsetVal += *Offset;
6738 auto Op0 = GEP_T->getOperand(0)->stripPointerCasts();
6739 if (Op0 == Ptr) {
6740 HasSameBase = true;
6741 break;
6742 }
6743 GEP_T = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(Op0);
6744 }
6745 if (!HasSameBase)
6746 return None;
6747 return OffsetVal;
6748 };
6749
6750 if (GEP1) {
6751 auto Offset = getOffsetFromBase(GEP1, Ptr2);
6752 if (Offset)
6753 return -*Offset;
6754 }
6755 if (GEP2) {
6756 auto Offset = getOffsetFromBase(GEP2, Ptr1);
6757 if (Offset)
6758 return Offset;
6759 }
6760
6761 // Right now we handle the case when Ptr1/Ptr2 are both GEPs with an identical
6762 // base. After that base, they may have some number of common (and
6763 // potentially variable) indices. After that they handle some constant
6764 // offset, which determines their offset from each other. At this point, we
6765 // handle no other case.
6766 if (!GEP1 || !GEP2 || GEP1->getOperand(0) != GEP2->getOperand(0))
6767 return None;
6768
6769 // Skip any common indices and track the GEP types.
6770 unsigned Idx = 1;
6771 for (; Idx != GEP1->getNumOperands() && Idx != GEP2->getNumOperands(); ++Idx)
6772 if (GEP1->getOperand(Idx) != GEP2->getOperand(Idx))
6773 break;
6774
6775 auto Offset1 = getOffsetFromIndex(GEP1, Idx, DL);
6776 auto Offset2 = getOffsetFromIndex(GEP2, Idx, DL);
6777 if (!Offset1 || !Offset2)
6778 return None;
6779 return *Offset2 - *Offset1;
6780}
